At this point, after being promoted to VP of Product and VP of Experience, =
respectively, the Board put Ben and me in the Office of the CEO. For our fi=
rst board meeting, we put together what must have been one of the most comp=
lex board decks in history to explain what we were doing and why it was wor=
king. We were so proud. Our Board members smiled and nodded along. Turns ou=
t, they were grinfucking us until they could find an adult to put in the CE=
O slot, one who could simplify the business enough to make it profitable at=
 the company level.=C2=A0
They found their guy, and when the new CEO came in, he got to work simplify=
ing. As two examples:
Monthly Only. Bigger monthly spaces brought in more revenue, more consisten=
tly, so we focused on acquiring bigger spaces that would be used exclusivel=
y for monthly, and even yearly, offerings.=C2=A0
Brokers. Our CEO learned that most commercial real estate is rented through=
