cussed ways that being undifferentiated impacts a company.=C2=A0
We went from being product-led to being sales-led. When you=E2=80=99re sell=
ing the same thing as everyone else, the only ways to win are by lowering p=
rices or =E2=80=A6 selling better than everyone else? This has a bunch of i=
ts own negative consequences, like letting sales dictate the design of spac=
es, making overly big concessions for customers, and putting burdens on the=
