here was a huge talent drain from the company. I left at the end of 2019.=
=C2=A0
These are obviously just my views of the situation. Forces beyond Breather=
=E2=80=99s control certainly hurt the company=E2=80=99s prospects. WeWork=
=E2=80=99s botched IPO in 2019 froze the funding market for anything that l=
ooked like WeWork. COVID froze the office market completely in 2020. And in=
 May 2021, after raising over $120 million, Breather was sold for parts to =
Industrious [ https://substack.com/redirect/7f264bd5-7ede-485a-bba4-85ebb84=
c9ab3?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] =
for $3 million. Maybe the new strategy would have worked in a different mar=
ket environment. I might like complexity a bit too much.
But having to go into work every day and face my team after the magic and m=
otivation had been sapped from all of us taught me that differentiation is =
