ive;"><strong>Story 3: Personal Monopoly</strong></h4><p style=3D"color: #4=
04040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">I&#8217;ve =
told this third story before, although maybe not through this exact lens, s=
o I&#8217;ll tell the quick version now.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: #40404=
0; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>During my=
 last year at Breather, when I no longer had the complex problem of buildin=
g a differentiated network to chew on, I decided that I wanted to start wri=
ting again. I&#8217;d written a couple of blog posts and stashed them in my=
 Medium drafts folder, but I wanted to do it more regularly and actually pu=
blish, so when I saw </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/66ad37=
0a-7eaa-423a-9570-f4fb75486fee?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjml=
XXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel=3D"" style=3D"color: #404040; text-decoration: =
